David Prutton leaves Leeds to sign for Colchester
Prutton scored from 25 yards two minutes into his U's debut David Prutton has joined Colchester United on a free transfer after having his contract at Leeds terminated by mutual consent.The 28-year-old midfielder scored on his U's debut against MK Dons after agreeing a loan deal last week. He could not play in the League One fixture between the two sides on Saturday, which Leeds won 2-0. Prutton has signed a contract that will keep him at Colchester until the end of the season. Bookmark with: Delicious Digg reddit Facebook StumbleUpon What are these?
